FBIS4-16810 "drsov076_a_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-076 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Foreign Ministry Denies Severing Ties With FRY Foreign Ministry Denies Severing Ties With FRY LD2004114694 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network in Russian 1100 GMT 20 Apr 94 LD2004114694 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel Network Russian BFN [From the "Novosti" newscast] [Text] There are many rumors about Russia's position in the Yugoslav conflict. Specifically, today the Foreign Ministry denied a report on a possible severance of diplomatic relations between Moscow and Belgrade. Yevgeniy Podkolzin, commander of Russian airborne landing troops, described as speculations reports on a withdrawal of the Russian battalion of Blue Helmets from Sarajevo. He said that this issue has not even been discussed. Also, a group of Russian servicemen was dispatched there yesterday, and today it was followed by another one. Russian Blue Berets have been serving with UN peace-keeping forces in Yugoslavia for over two years. Two Russian battalions are stationed in the eastern sector and in Sarajevo area. Now their personnel is being relieved, which is a normal rotation. Two hundred paras are replacing their comrades in the hottest spot in the world. They have left for Yugoslavia from Ryazan.
